caption.text:
"MALINNGG"
.
Itulah hal pertama yang terdengar setiap kali gw dateng ke kelas nomor 7 angkatan 2015 ini. Pertama kali kenal mereka semua di semester ganjil, pas gw jadi asma jejadiannya @ari_arisantosa di kelas Drawing Principles. Isinya bener2 mahasiswa begundal kreatif, dari ketua kelasnya yang ngaku "alay", anak Ciater yang suka skate board, 2 artis Starlite, cewek otomotif, kumpulan anak-anak gila anime, dan.... ya banyak lah, sampe gw gak bisa sebutin satu-satu. Tapi dari itu semua, kelas berinisial "G" ini isinya anak-anak kreatif, gila, begundal, kompak dan koplak. 1 tahun gw kenal mereka dan 1 tahun gw abiskan untuk ngebantu mereka meraih tujuan mereka di UMN.
.
Gw juga belajar banyak dari lo semua, jadi makasih banyak atas kegilaan kalian semua. Makin-makinin gilanya ya, karena kalian DKV-Gila. Semoga kegilaan kalian bisa membawa kalian ke tujuan dan impian kalian di masa depan.
.
Dan satu hal aja: jangan (berhenti) panggil gw maling! Asma lo udah gila sekarang.
.
Photo thanks to @kyorukii
Edited by me
.
#dkv #umn #digital #publishing #g1 #begundal #gila #mahasiswagila #asisten #malingsial

Oh yeah, I did forget to show my #inktober day 2 "Behind The Making". To put it short, first I draw a car sketch with a blue-colored pencil (pencil that most comic maker use to sketch, or by animator to render an animation process). With the help from @vronkz and @mario.hartawan, then I made the car details and shade it with 0.3 and 0.5 drawing pen (I only use them because I don't bring others, so yea, sorry). I'm still learning about car design, though. And I'm not really good at drawing, yet. So, I'm open to any kind of critiques and comments. Thank you guys :) #inktoberindonesia #progress #sketch #bluecoloredpencil #drawingpen #car #stepbystep #learning #design

caption.text:
My another latepost on GAIKINDO INDONESIA INTERNATIONAL AUTO SHOW. 
This is one of the car we spotted in GIIAS, namely Daihatsu Wake. This Kei Cars (Japanese terminology for small cars with small CC, presumably 900cc and below) is one of my favorite cars that Daihatsu has ever produced. At the first glance, it looks like a smaller version of Luxio, yet cooler. It's CVT (means it's automatic transmission) and this one is modified with BBS rims and MOMO steering wheels.

I took my time by sit on the driver seat. IT'S AWESOME! It's comfort, and the dashboard looks cool. The MOMO steering wheel just make it really cool. 
The back seat also provide its comfort; the leg room is really big. I can't imagine that this small car can provide a great leg room that almost looks like a refular cars around. 
Rumors that this car will be produced in Indonesia (I saw Daihatsu Facebook Page claiming to see the price on the nearest dealer), but I'm not sure abut it. However, if it's true, the I'll add it to my wishlist. 
Thank you, Daihatsu. Thank you, Gaikindo. 
#gaikindo #indonesia #international #auto #show #daihatsu #wake #kei #cars #ice #bsd #friends #hangout #japan #bbs #momo
